		<h2><a href="http://xbox.about.com/b/2013/02/08/dead-space-3-review-x360.htm" zT="1/1jS">Dead Space 3 Review (X360)</a></h2>
		
		<div class="date">Friday February 8, 2013</div>	
	<div class="entry"><p><img src="http://0.tqn.com/d/xbox/1/0/E/t/deadspace3box.jpg" alt="" hspace="5" align="right" /><br />
 Recent history would show that adding co-op to an established horror franchise might not be a good idea (Resident Evil), but EA and Visceral had faith that it would be different with Dead Space 3.  For the most part, they were right.  Playing co-op actually doesn't change things that much, and other additions to the experience really make this one of the most interesting and replayable Dead Space titles yet.  And if you are still dead set against co-op, the solo experience here is pretty much exactly what you'd expect from the series.  Well done, Visceral.  We have all of the details here in our full review.</p>

